Architects have understood that offices also need custody
The administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of Arch.Design.
No one would say that he also hides inside a small garden with all of his own facilities: color walls, creative furniture and even a miniature park on the outdoor terrace.
Since October last year, the children of Arch.Design employees can visit her.
Arch.Design, from which many famous buildings of Brno emerged, thought from the first sketches of the Avriopoint building to include a space for its mining.
About 90 people work in the company, mainly at the age of baby boom and wanted to allow architects and designers to return to work soon after maternity.
Along with the possibility of enjoying a reduced schedule, the yard is one of the benefits Arch offers.Design your workers in the context of your social program.
Constructors and architects thus have the opportunity to combine a demanding profession with the care of children.
Mining was an idea of Arch.Designu's own employees and, with the support of the management, they managed to obtain funding from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The company's retail business is financed through the European Social Fund under the Operational Programme of Human Resources and Employment, as well as the State budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding granted (over 2.8 million Czech crowns) they were able to purchase equipment and, after two years, to hire qualified personnel and services.
When the funding is exhausted (two years), Arch.Design has an obligation to keep the mini-care facility in operation with its own funds for three years.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and the company Economy Rating contributed to the submission of the funding application.
Children's attention is in the hands of qualified staff; a nurse and a teacher of the Ministry of Education are also present all day. The care is now home to children with no age limit, although most of them are less than three years old.
Since this is a "miniguardery", it can only accommodate a maximum of five children at the same time, although with shifts it is more during the day.
The operation of the guard is flexible to adapt to the needs of parents and children of all workers have the same right to use the guard, regardless of the hierarchy within the company.
