Can the citizen tend a bridge to unite the divisions?
After a notable campaign of invective and negativity, this week has triggered a bit of civilism in Washington.
Is it a prelude to genuine future bipartisan cooperation or an illusory moment before a rapid return to the partyist struggle in the capital?
The Tuesday meeting between President Obama and the leaders of Congress did not lead to any progress in the major issues to be addressed during the upcoming meeting.
