People should visit Visa Applicant Service Centres prior to their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower as well as the waiting time.
From 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing a visa in the United States Embassy and consulate will be changed.
With the new procedure, most applicants will have to go to Visa Applicant Service Centres (ASC) for their English stamps before their interview in the Consular Section.
The staff of the ASC will receive the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer will it be necessary to make a payment to conclude the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and more so that the message service deliver the document.
The vacuum cleaner will make only one single payment that will cover all three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for petitioned visas (including temporary workers ' visas) and $390 for traders and investors ' visas.
People wishing to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain at less than in the past.
Similarly, applicants for visas in the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and New Laredo will no longer pay the extra $26 service fee.
